The agreement has been primarily drafted from the point of view of the production company. However, it has been drafted using a fair and balanced approach with regard to the obligations it imposes on the artists, in order to attempt to ensure that the agreement cannot be argued to be an unconscionable bargain so as to be unenforceable. However, this note includes some guidance as to when the artists might seek to negotiate alternative or additional wording.
